                            <comment id="13528944" author="knutanders" created="Tue, 11 Dec 2012 13:12:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Do we need a separate release note for this issue, or would it suffice to mention hard upgrade in the release note for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5232&quot; title=&quot;Put a stern README file in log and seg0 directories to warn users of corrpution they will cause if they touch files there&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-5232&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-5232&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13530717" author="mamtas" created="Thu, 13 Dec 2012 06:08:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Release note attached to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5232&quot; title=&quot;Put a stern README file in log and seg0 directories to warn users of corrpution they will cause if they touch files there&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-5232&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-5232&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; will cover the release note for this jira too. Because of this, I have removed release notes needed flag from this jira.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13603412" author="rhillegas" created="Fri, 15 Mar 2013 14:30:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I deleted the release note for this issue since it was agreed that the note attached to &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5232&quot; title=&quot;Put a stern README file in log and seg0 directories to warn users of corrpution they will cause if they touch files there&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-5232&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-5232&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; is sufficient. For some reason the release note generator seems to be including release notes even though the release-note-needed flag is turned off.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
